As the Sydney Summer abruptly ended, with a deluge of rain,one of the plus sides, is the annual release of an Autumn Seasonal from @doctorsordersbrewing.  This year, Doc has canned ‘Electrolyte Serum’ a rhubarb infused gose, that was originally brewed for the 2nd birthday of The Alehouse. Reproduced for SCBW opening Gala Party Oct 2014.  The gose style was a practically extinct style of top fermented Gose beer that originated in Goslar, Germany, but started to re-emerge in the 80’s.  Then Doctors Orders were the first to commercially introduce the style to Australia in 2010.  Since then Doc has brewed several versions, resulting in Electrolyte Serum becoming their 2nd canned release.  Upon opening the nose has a dominant lemon characteristic with some coriander.  On taste the immediate tartness is well balanced with the saltiness that dries the palate on finish.  The rhubarb compliments not just to the sharpness, but a subtle sweetness that adds to the balance of the beer.  At 4% ABV, and while the Sun may not be out at the moment, a 4pk of these, sunshine or not, would go down well regardless of the weather.

BANKSTOWN ARTS CENTRE  Opened in February 2011, the Bankstown Arts Centre is a cultural facility, where artists and community groups collaborate to explore ideas and learn, create and experience contemporary community based arts.  The Arts Centre provides accommodation for professional and amateur arts organisations, as well as a range of flexible spaces to develop arts practice. Resident organisations at Bankstown Arts Centre include Urban Theatre Projects, Bankstown Youth Development Service, Bankstown Art Society, Bankstown and District Lapidary Club Inc. and Bankstown Theatrical Society. J’ai eu cette impression de vivre dans un univers parallèle en voyant toutes ces personnes épanouies dans leur environnement en pratiquant le boulot, métro, dodo, afin de créer un certain confort. Vous savez cette façon de vivre ou tous les jours nous nous réveillons dans la même pièce et suivons la même routines, pour vivre le même jour qu’hier. J’ai arrêté de réfléchir au pourquoi certains réussissent et moi non. Vous êtes surement plus intelligent, vous avez surement plus de talent, mais pour ma part je ne vois que deux manières d’être riche : la première est d’avoir tout ce que je veux, et la seconde d’être satisfait de ce que j’ai ! Cette impression bizarroïde d’être étranger dans ce monde, comme si j’avais été conçu dans un moule different, désolé Maman je ne remets pas en cause ta conception, mais je n’arrive vraiment pas à concevoir une vie à cette sauce “work-life balance”(3). Dans ma réalité parallèle je suis persuadé que je peux vivre du stricte minimum tout en voyageant dans des véhicules sans confort, sans pour autant passer pour un marginal. Le voyage pour moi se résume à un van, une guitare, une boite de thon pour se rassasier, une douche froide tous les deux jours tout en se sentant comme Hamdane ben Mohammed Al Maktoum.  En France, je ne peux pas dire que je me sens concerné par cette description. Equipé de vêtement à la mode estimé surement à plus d’un SMIC, la coupe toujours bien entretenue après une bonne douche chaude de plusieurs minutes, des soirées à la “m’as tu vu” à n’en plus finir le weekend, une voiture bichonnée et pleins d’autres choses matérialistes et inutiles qui me donne un semblant d’image auprès de mes 700 amis sur Facebook. Justement hier je suis sorti, alors aujourd’hui je me tag sur les dernières images de la soirée avec des commentaires jouissifs pour montrer aux autres que c’était « la soirée de l’année ». Je sors mon i-truc pour poster la vidéo de la performance du i-D.J., cette même performance que j’ai regardé derrière l’écran de mon téléphone, oubliant de profiter du show en direct. backpacker inconnu #backpacker #sydney #australia #backpackerstory #backpackerphotography #traveler #travel #selfdrive

Вчера я первый раз была в казино 😄 И даже играла в рулетку с настоящими деньгами (а не как в монополии) 😂 Слава богу, деньги были не мои и я к ним все равно больше относилась как к просто поинтам, знаю, я ужасный человек 🙈 Рулетка оказывается так весело, а я даже и не подозревала. Но больше меня порадовала китайская старенькая женщина сидевшая за игральным столом рядом. К слову говоря, одета была как с бежицкого рынка, но сумку LV 🤘🏼. И она мне очень душещипательно рассказывала, что сегодня не её день и что она уже проиграла 45к. Внимание, был только час ночи! Я конечно же сочувственно ей кивала, а лицо выражало мое полное понимание всей её беды, как будто и со мной такие неудачные дни переодически случаются 😂 Но это же пиздец ребят, однокомнатная квартирка в Брянске была проиграна за один вечер! И чтоб вы понимали она не остановилась и пошла спать, нет, она сказала, что это видишь ли стол неудачный и ей надо его сменить, и ушла в неизвестном направление 😱

Why your skin absolutely Loves  IV Vitamin C 👩‍⚕️👩‍⚕️👩‍⚕️. REASON #1: vitamin C is a key element in the production of collagen, which is a vital structural protein of the skin. So, by applying vitamin C topically having it intravenously. or digesting it internally, you’re boosting the creation of collagen, which helps to promote smoother, younger-looking skin.  REASON #2: vitamin C is an antioxidant, and this means it can help reduce skin damage caused by free radicals, improving the texture of your skin and reducing wrinkles as a result.  REASON #3: highly-concentrated vitamin C accelerates the skin’s cell turnover mechanism, breaking up dark spots and dull skin tone as a result. This means you’re left with a brighter, more illuminated complexion.  REASON #4: not only does vitamin C help break down current pigmentation, but it also helps prevent new dark spots from appearing by fighting the formation of concentrated melanin patches.  REASON #5: vitamin c acts as a gentle exfoliator, which helps to erase surface marks while smoothing it at the same time. "Quando ero bambina, per il mio compleanno i miei genitori mi lasciavano invitare le amiche  a casa. Avremmo guardato un film, uno di quelli della Disney; probabilmente Il Re Leone, avremmo pianto alla morte di Mufasa e indossato un lucida labbra con i brillantini. Mia madre ci avrebbe riempito di patatine e avrebbe commissionato alla pasticceria la mia torta Sailor Moon.  Avrei riso, perché i miei genitori volevano così. È  come sentirsi onnipotenti, sai, riuscire a far ridere una persona.  Ti pare di esser Dio, o meglio, superiore a lui, perché che cazzo lui ha i poteri, tu no, sei un mero pezzo di carne, tu sei solo umano.  Uomini, questo quel che siamo.  Basiamo la nostra vita a compiere i doveri del lavoro, soldi a palate , per altri il vuoto nelle tasche. Ci dimentichiamo di respirare, di guardare quel tramonto fuori dal treno ché si ha sonno, mi devo svegliare presto, spegni la luce, ti tocco domani.  A volte mi basta guardarti, per esser felice. Sei come la primavera dopo l’inverno, i petali di seta sull'asfalto, i colori sul bianco. Tu che impari l’inglese con I tuoi modi maldestri, tu che piangi di notte senza avvisarmi, tu che mi prendi per mano, ti prego andiamo al parco a giocare.  Quando ero bambina, I fiori sbocciavano a Marzo. Ora, muoiono ad Aprile". {#homesick #chasinglight #instagood #igaustralia #watchthisinstagood #vscocam #postthepeople #artspace #makemoments #igmasters #AOV #artofvisuals #seeforyourself #huffpostgram #teamtravelers #livelevel #justgoshoot #home #tbt #shotoniphone #folkgood #iphonesia #likeforlike #follow4follow #selfie #medstudent #medlife #sydney

The CHAPEL by John Lobb is a #workofart.  Fashioned from a single piece of leather with no back seam, parallel buckles, squared toe and sweeping lines, this shoe is sure to get you noticed, because, as I've always said, YOUR SHOES SHOULD BE THE MOST EXPENSIVE ITEM IN YOUR WARDROBE!  I can imagine walking into a meeting or to a date, you're impeccably dressed, a tad cutting edge, but oh so fashion forward.  On your feet... These shoe's.  Gasp!💜💜💚💜💜. ABOUT:  John Lobb has been making the finest shoes and boots for gentlemen since 1866 in London and 1902 in Paris. Its rich heritage is reinforced by timeless qualities of craftsmanship, service and style - attributes that are now available to a wider international John Lobb audience. The company continues to maintain its bespoke shoe-making tradition in Paris, while also retaining core bespoke principles in the manufacture of its expanding ready-to-wear collection of shoes and leather goods.  PRICE: $1,750.00. *  8000 Last. *  Single Leather Sole. *  Supplied with a shoe tree.  PHOTOS: @johnlobb 👈👈👍👍 you are a genius.  Everything I've seen in the collection's I've fallen in love with. Dê passo no escuro. E você vai enxergar sua vida de longe com uma clareza nunca antes vista. Caminhe mais pouco. Mais um tanto. Por horas, por dias. E vai perceber que o silêncio é tão confortável quanto uma conversa com um desconhecido. Aliás, o desconhecido passará a ser um breve momento- transitório- antes de se tornar conhecido. Porque você vai deixar de temer tudo o que não conhece. Vai se despir de roupas, preconceitos e verdades. Continue a jornada sem entender nada do que é dito ao seu redor. Não tem problema se você não falar nem uma palavra. Você vai aprender de uma vez por todas que não importa o que estão dizendo. A voz aí de dentro é a única que vai falar mais alto. Liberte-se de todo o peso que você insiste em carregar sem necessidade. Vai demorar um pouco para aprender sobre isso. Seus ombros vão doer muito antes que você decida jogar qualquer coisa fora. Mas uma vez que você desocupe um pequeno espaço, vai sentir vontade de desocupar muito mais. Você vai querer espaço livre, folha em branco e costas leves. Não existe outra forma de ser livre, senão, livrando-se. Livre-se para ser livre, combinado? E uma vez livre, a liberdade vai te acompanhar aonde você estiver. Não precisa necessariamente ir até a Patagônia para respirar novos ares. Mas se puder ir, vá. Mas volte. E na volta, quando estiver em casa se preparando para dormir, certifique-se que a porta está destrancada e aberta para quando você quiser sair... 2 anos atrás eu cheguei em Sydney. Quanta coisa aconteceu! 본다이에 이은 시드니 비치 탐험 두 번째. 맨리비치의 코르소 거리. 비치 앞의 스트릿 구경하는 재미가 꽤  쏠쏠하다.  생각해보면 여기는 상가들의 간판이 다 판대기(?)라 저녁5시 이후만 되도 어두컴컴 해 져서 (우리나라 처럼 네온사인이 없음) 다들 퇴근하고 가족과 시간을 지내는 것 같다. 진정한 저녁이 있는 삶.  본다이가 젊은이들의 성지라면 (그래서 해운대같다고 한거다. 막 헐벗고 다니는 전세계 몸짱 써퍼들은 본다이에 다 모여서 젊은이들이 거리에 넘치니까ㅋ) 맨리는 가족과 연인, 노부부가 삼삼오오 추억을 만드는 곳.  그나저나 여기 하늘은 언제 찍어도 예쁘구나. #맨리비치 #코르소거리 #시드니 #호주 #여행스타그램 #일상 #산책 #manlybeach #thecorso #sydney #australia

어딘가모르게 아저씨같이 생긴 원숭이,, #타롱가동물원  호주에서 마지막날은 동물원에 놀이공원에 잔디밭 전망대까지 내가 좋아하는 것만 꽉꽉 채워서 보내려고 했는데 비가!!!!!! 하필 저날!!! 🌪 사실 가기전에 일기예보에선 시드니에서의 8일내내 비가 온다고 했지만 역시 이 나라나 저 나라나 일기예보는 다 거짓말이였다 하지만 마지막날 정확하게 맞아버린거임 여기 사람들 비 웬만큼 오는거 아니고서는 다 맞고다니던데 때려붓기 시작하니까 좀 피하더라 다들 가까운 천막이나 지붕으로 뛰어들어갔는데 나는,,, 또 하필,, 커플이랑 같은 천막에서 비 피하게됨 👫💃,,, 둘만의 로맨틱하고 오붓한 시간 방해한거같아 넘 뻘쭘하고 민망했는데 나중에 커플이 먼저 힐위꼬우~~ 이러고 뛰어감 ㅎ 유쾌하시네요 비 피하면서 카톡하는데 그 다음주 월요일에 내가 학교에 나가야한다는게 안믿겨서 똥루었다 여튼 그 비 피한곳이 저 마다가스카 원숭이 놀이터 앞이였음  호주 동물원 넘 개방적이고 동물이랑 사람 거리가 가까워서 놀랐는데 그만큼 관리도 철저하고 직원도 봉사자도 많아서 신기했음  동물들 보고있으면 초록조끼입은 봉사자들이 슥 다가와서 이쳐메이징 롸잇? 이러고 말걸어줌 여튼 좋았다 동물원은 여러번에 걸쳐서 올릴거시다 끗  #소구의_여행일기_호주 #소구의_여행일기_시드니

#art#to#sky#saturday#sydney#daringharbour#Australia#sunshine#shopping#relaxingtime#onmyway#street#people#beauty  오늘 작년에 만난 친구들과 서리힐즈에 가서 식사를 하고 같이 쇼핑까지 했는 데.. 나에게 너 영어 좀 더 해야겠다. 뭐 이런 충고를 받은 느낌이다. 학교 따라가는 것은 그렇다고 치고 쓰기보다 말하기가 어렵다는 거.. 내가 유독 쓰기 논술 시험에 강해서 그럴 수도 있지만..외국 자체에 뉘앙스.. 그것도 잘 모르겠고 여기 산지 두달 되어서.. 잘한다는 것도 이상하다.. 대부분 친구들은 1년이상 거주 했고 원래 영어를 잘했다고 하는 데 나는 아닌 걸.. 그냥 한국에 살던 20대였을 뿐.. 다른 사람들은 내가 다른 나라 그것도 호주에 산다고 좋아하지만 나의 삶은 그리 평화롭지 못하다. 하루 하루의 감정이 매일 다르고 지금 살고 있는 현재에 대해 또 생각한다. 여기나 한국이나 키 큰 사람이 신기한 지.. 뭘 그리도 내 키랑 국적을 묻는 지.. 우리 부모님이 주신 나의 키가 매우 부러운 지..

People are maybe wondering why am i posting so many coffee with milk photos,here's their answer;i love coffee,latte art and the esthetical view of the work and designs i do,it requires knowledge,artisan techniques,years of mastery and experience,passion and love of coffee,it requires some machines and tools yes but guess what,it requires a barista too...so sad that i had to explain and so glad that i did.it seems easy but it's not...it seems routine but it varies...every single cup is another chance of training for bettering urself and all of them have different stories...i do have love,passion and respect to my job,me respecting my work means respecting coffee as the nature's one of the best gifts,respecting coffee means respecting the history of humanity...respecting coffee means,respecting the labor behind it...industry workers,the farmers and the roasters,baristas,machines and tools manufacturers,trainers, judges and their families...before being judgemental please try learning the hinterlands of what u r really critisizing...pls be more respectful to ur self first and then the coffee,mark my words,u will be more happy that way.enough being this deductive,thx a lot everyone and have fun on ur sweet sunday.😆coffe coffee coffee time☕⛾kahve zamani!!!☕⛾ #coffee #flatwhite #coffeelover #coffeelove #tbt #coffeebreak #kadikoy #amsterdam #instacool #coffeehouse #coffeeshop #cafe #instamood #sydney #paris #istanbul #cafetime #latte #latteart #latteartist #barista #baristaskills #cappuccino #marmarauniversitesi #art #drink #artisancoffee #specialtycoffee #istanbuluniversitesi #instagram

........ Bakmayın böyle seyirlik bir uçurum olduğuna bir çok insan hayata veda etmiş burdan. İntiharlarıyla ünlü uppppuzun bir uçurum şeridi. Hatta biz gittiğimizde yere bırakılmış çiçeklerle mum vardı 😔İnsan bu güzelliğe bakarak nasıl veda eder diye düşünmeden edemedim. Biçok önlem alınmasına rağmen maalesef doğumla birlikte aldıkları en güzel hediyeden bir uçurumdan kendilerini bırakarak vazgeçiyor insanlar. (Allah aklımıza fikrimize sahip olma yetimizi almasın elimizden) Onun dışında Avustralya'nın en eski balıkçı köyüymüş ama şimdi çok güzel evlerin, restorantların, beachlerin olduğu  popülaritesi çok yüksek bir yer. Kalamar ve karides hastası olan ben en leziz kalamarı burada yedim diyebilirim. Taze ve leziz deniz mahsülleri ile neden ünlü olduğunu anlìadım yani 😀 Bu fotoğrafı çektiğim yerin arkasında muhteşem bir körfez ve insanların çimlerine uzandığı yemyeşil bir park var. This Easter school holidays keep the kids moving at Kids in the Park from 8 - 23 April (inclusive). Parents often feel the pressure to provide their kids with action-packed holidays which can bring about financial stress – however keeping the kids amused doesn’t need to be expensive. Sydney Olympic Park has a range of fun activities to keep kids entertained and active during the NSW Easter school holidays without breaking the bank.  The Kids in the Park program, has something for everyone with a program to suit all tastes, ages and budgets with more than 50 activities, including 14 FREE, 7 NEW and 12 good-value options at $25 or less per person.  For full details, visit kidsinthepark.com.au (orsydneyolympicpark.com.au). Also, check-outSydney Olympic Park’s YouTube Channel, follow@olympicpark_syd on Twitter and@SydOlympicPark on Instagram or visit theSydney Olympic Park page on Facebook.  #sydney #schoolholidays #sydolympicpark #kidsinthepark #kids #easter #fun #play #kid #children #boy #free #child  #schoolholidayactivities

The Naked Grouse enriches the flavours of Scotland’s favourite whisky by maturing in sun dried sherry oak casks. The influence of our quality first-fill sherry casks develops a deep russet appearance and an aroma that melds black cherries, cocoa and oak. The taste experience is sublimely smooth with famous trade-mark dried fruits yielding to cinnamon sticks and nutmeg. The sweet finale is rich in dark chocolate with a spicy, orange finish. A fine example of the blender’s art, it is best enjoyed neat or as a classic “Old Fashioned " . Bardwell Park Cellars has this glorious Whisky , first among specialist wine and spirits merchants. Chris is reading Mr A his story tonight. And I'm figuring out where to hang my new KD I found today!  This framed poster is huge, and in perfect condition and dwarfed 5ft me when I had to carry it to my car.  Contrary to IG posts, I'm not always 'on the hunt' for Ken Done pieces! But lots of people have been asking me where I find all this Ken Done - and honestly it's a combo of luck, education and #locationlocation.  I'm really open to travelling to different areas in Melbourne, and I find that the older demographic areas usually have a higher concentration of KD. Similarly I personally have a (weird) visual memory and usually I can quickly scan and recognise a print quite quickly (usually from searching ebay, etsy, gumtree, artbooks etc)  While clothes are probably the most difficult to find, Linen, Kitchen Linens, scarves and bags are normally the best place to start. Today I am another year older and it's days like today that introspection comes easiest. Lately as a part of my endeavours to build a little side hustle, I've started to follow some really cool people on social media. Each are passionate about the environment and  are concerned about the amount of waste that we as humans produce. In a climate where it often feels like you're among the minority, where the battle is all up hill, where people often turn a blind eye, it is heartening to know that these people exist and are doing every little bit they can to make change happen. This is what drives me. My greatest hope is that I can inspire others to re-imagine how they are doing things, to make small (or big) changes and to educate themselves and their families.  So, here's a tip for you: carry your own re-usable cup! Ask your favourite barista to make your coffee in your cup, not a disposable. You don't give up coffee - nobody wants a mass of caffeine deprived tyrants roaming the streets...but this small change will help to reduce the 1 billion odd coffee cups (most of which contain plastic)  making it into landfill in Australian each year. #travelmug #reusablecup #environmentallyfriendly #reducereuserecycle #stopthewaste #reducelandfill #mothernature #ifnotforyouthenwho #doitforaustralia #doitfortheearth #sydneycity #sydney #australia #norwex

APRIL 11, 2017 2:08 A.M EST, 7:08 AM #London, and 4:08 PM in #Sydney. The #PinkMoon, also known as April's #FullMoon. Although we won't literally see the color #pink when we gaze above tonight, April's full moon is called the pink moon because it was how our #indigenous peoples here in the U.S. kept time and track of changes in #nature: with this moon, it was the arrival of #mosspink, one of the first #springtime flowers, signifying #change. "As above, so below." Below is a picture I took last year at #Keukenhof, the #GardenOfEurope in Lisse, the #Netherlands. There is only a short period of time each year to experience Keukenhof, and it is so #beautiful! A truly stunning array of flowers in all different shades of color...it is a must for your #bucketlist!  Now, from an #astrological standpoint, the Pink Moon will be in 22 degrees #Libra. Wherever Libra falls in your natal chart, you can expect issues related to the theme of that particular astrological house...and these may be the issues that have finally reached their culmination, so the Universe may request or even demand #change from you.  For your #meditation of the full #moon, think of what changes are needed in your #life, and if you have your natal chart and can see where 22 degrees Libra falls in it, all the better.  But look to #nature for #inspiration on where these changes are leading you, just as the Native Americans did before dreadful "time management" became a buzzword in today's world. Judgment and uncertainty, makes decisions that sometimes isn't the right one all because of the feeling of fear. Fear to prove that you're happy? The fear of being who you are? The only fear of not pleasing? But ultimately when you're well and happy, family and friends are there to encourage, to share this happiness! A smile should have a smile in return and to give a hand must be caught to be listened to, advised or helped!  Be respectful and loving because there is nothing wrong to be in love! Checking airmail bags for the first airmail flight to England from Sydney in November 1931. The aircraft, an Avro 618 Ten named the Southern Sun, was one of five aircraft that Australian National Airways owned. . www.CraftBreweries.com.au . BREWERY SHOWCASE - @4PinesBeer . ABOUT The love child of a post-surf beer and a casual conversation between a father and son – 4 Pines was born and the Brewpub Manly is where it all started. This week however, the Brewpub has grown - The Keller Door has opened, downstairs from the Brewpub. . With upstairs busting at the seams and having no more room to showcase all of their Core Range and Keller Door beers all at once, the brewpub was extended to create this one of kind Keller Door. Exclusively Keller Door beers and the Chefs have taken a leaf out of their brewers’ handbook and let their imaginations run wild, resulting in an eclectic, passion-filled menu. . This is a communal eating and drinking experience at its best, built around vibrant and diverse, small, large and feast size plates. It’s where family and friends end up with dirty hands, faces and grins. To enjoy, they’ve created an Armageddon proof* toasty warm log cabin – ready for an Armageddon proof* experience, tucked downstairs right beneath where it all began. . Apart from the venue in Manly, 4 Pines have also opened two other venues; The Truck Bar in their main brewery in Brookvale featuring 21 taps and the Public House Newport - a barrel aged beer room. . More info on their website. . *May not be Armageddon proof. . ADDRESS Shop 29 / 43-45 East Esplanade MANLY NSW 2095 . PHONE – 02 9976 2300 . HOURS The Manly Brewpub is open every day for lunch and dinner - Monday to Sunday 11:00 am until Late .
